   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON TWELVE THE DISPENSING FUNCTION</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OF THE TRIUNE GOD Scripture Reading: Rom 8:9-11, 14, 16; Eph 3:14, 16-17a, 19b; 4:6; John 15:1, 5, 26; 14:10, 17-20, 23; Heb 8:10-11; 1 John 2:27 OUTLINE God the Father: Being the source John 15:1b; Eph 3:14, 16a.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Abiding in us Eph 4:6.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>God the Son: Being the embodiment of the Father John 15:1a; 14:10.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Abiding in us and making His home in our hearts John 15:5a; Eph 3:17a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>God the Spirit: The reality of the Son John 14:17-20.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Dwelling in us Rom 8:11.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The Triune God the Father, the Son, and the Spirit dispensing Himself into our being Eph 3:14, 16-17a, 19b.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The dispensing function of the Triune God issuing in the sense of life: Through the law of life Heb 8:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>By the teaching of the anointing 1 John 2:27.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In our spirit mingled with the life-giving Spirit Rom 8:16, 14.</S>
   </TEXT>
